# The Docker build context is the repo root (docker-compose `context: .`), so this
# is the .dockerignore that actually applies. Without it, `COPY . .` in the build
# stage ships the host's node_modules and .git into the image — slow, and a source
# of "works on my machine" drift when a host-built native module overwrites the one
# the image installed for its own platform.

# Dependencies — reinstalled inside the image for the image's own platform.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build output — rebuilt in the image.
dist
**/dist
.next
**/.next
build
**/build

# Version control and CI.
.git
.github

# Secrets and local env — NEVER in an image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Logs, coverage, caches.
*.log
coverage
**/coverage
.turbo
.cache

# Editor / OS noise.
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Docs and local-only tooling don't belong in a runtime image.
# (The API build only needs source, prisma, and the contracts package.)
